# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Firebase Configuration
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This file shows an EXAMPLE of what environment variables you need to set.
# DO NOT commit this file with actual secrets!
# Copy this to .env and fill in your own values.
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Path to your Firebase service account JSON file
# You get this from: Firebase Console → Project Settings → Service Accounts → Generate New Private Key
# Place the downloaded JSON file in your project root and set this path:
GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=./serviceAccountKey.json

# Firebase Realtime Database URL
# You get this from: Firebase Console → Realtime Database → Overview (copy the URL)
# Example: https://your-project-12345.firebaseio.com
FIREBASE_DATABASE_URL=https://console.firebase.google.com/u/0/project/gymsensor-ce1ec/database/gymsensor-ce1ec-default-rtdb/data/~2F